text: South side of Dobratsch as seen from Hohenthurn. Dobratsch (Slovenian: Dobrač) or the Villacher Alps (Slovenian: Beljaščica) is a mountain range in the Carinthia region of Austria. Its peak is above sea level and it is a protected natural park. It forms the foothills of the Gailtal Alps and is immediately west of the town of Villach.
